    "163622d9-209e-44c3-bfe1-bf7145ab92e8": {
      "type": "article-image-texts-block-new",
      "blocks": {
        "template--16978255249660__163622d9-209e-44c3-bfe1-bf7145ab92e8-heading-1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "headingtext": "<p>Nafees: Nuances in the Art of Jewelry Making<\/p>"
          }
        },
        "template--16978255249660__163622d9-209e-44c3-bfe1-bf7145ab92e8-texts-1": {
          "type": "texts",
          "settings": {
            "fullinfotext": "<p>In the next chapter of our odyssey, an exhibit unveiled the alchemy of fine jewelry making. Titled Nafees, it took the guests on a visually immersive journey that showcased some of the nuances of jewelry-making that we incorporate into our pieces, which elevate the piece to the extraordinary.<\/p><p>They experienced the magic of gemstones and pearls, the <em>sukshma <\/em>hero of jewelry; the beauty of the nuances of the <em>ghat <\/em>(the gold framework into which the stones are set); the <em>adaa <\/em>in different elements stringing such as <em>fungar<\/em>—tiny gold cups cradling pearls topped with enamel beads, <em>laria<\/em>—minute units where seed pearls dance on small gold wires, gracefully culminating in enamel beads at their feet, <em>pirai<\/em>—stringing together seed pearls and\/or stone beads to either border a unit or be suspended, giving movement to the piece; and the nuances that go when assembling a piece of jewelry (adding a <em>gaadi <\/em>behind a choker, for example).<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
