    "45a26bcd-88d7-4e39-a2d7-942fe86a06f2": {
      "type": "article-image-texts-block-new",
      "blocks": {
        "2291db07-c3c7-4e45-aff2-d6105a940f67": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "headingtext": "<p>Gufa and the Pichwai Gallery<\/p>"
          }
        },
        "template--16978255249660__45a26bcd-88d7-4e39-a2d7-942fe86a06f2-texts-1": {
          "type": "texts",
          "settings": {
            "fullinfotext": "<p>We had the fortune of visiting the Hussain-Doshi marvel, the Amdavad Ni Gufa, and having it to ourselves for almost an hour, and setting our eyes on the unreal Kamal Chowk, a reconstructed, and re-imagined pre-Mughal period mandapa originally crafted by the skilled stone artisans of Patan, now converted into a contemporary display space for Pichwais and miniatures from Amit Ambalal’s collection.<\/p><p><\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
